      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A minimum wage increase directly raises your labor costs, which can be a significant factor for small businesses, especially those with thin margins. While your rural location offers lower operating costs, higher wages still require you to adjust your budget to cover the increased payroll. You will likely need to either absorb some of the cost, slightly raise prices, or find ways to increase efficiency to maintain profitability.",
